msgid ""
"Please note that the Spring support in Quarkus does not start a Spring Application Context nor are any Spring infrastructure classes run.\n"
"Spring classes and annotations are only used for reading metadata and / or are used as user code method return types or parameter types.\n"
"What that means for end users, is that adding arbitrary Spring libraries will not have any effect. Moreover, Spring infrastructure\n"
"classes (like `org.springframework.beans.factory.config.BeanPostProcessor` , `org.springframework.context.ApplicationContext` for example) will not be executed.\n"
"Regarding the dependency injection in particular, Quarkus uses a Dependency Injection mechanism (called ArC) based on the https://jakarta.ee/specifications/cdi/4.1/jakarta-cdi-spec-4.1.html[Jakarta Contexts and Dependency Injection 4.1] specification. If you want to learn more about it, we recommend you to read the xref:cdi.adoc[Quarkus introduction to CDI] and the xref:cdi-reference.adoc#arc-configuration-reference[CDI reference guide]\n"
"The various Spring Boot test features are not supported by Quarkus. For testing purposes, please, check the xref:getting-started-testing.adoc[Quarkus testing guide]."
msgstr "Tenga en cuenta que el soporte de Spring en Quarkus no inicia un Contexto de AplicaciÃģn Spring ni se ejecuta ninguna clase de infraestructura Spring. Las clases y anotaciones de Spring sÃģlo se utilizan para leer metadatos y/o se utilizan como tipos de retorno de mÃĐtodos o tipos de parÃĄmetros de cÃģdigo de usuario. Lo que esto significa para los usuarios finales, es que aÃąadir bibliotecas Spring arbitrarias no tendrÃĄ ningÃšn efecto. AdemÃĄs, las clases de infraestructura de Spring (como `org.springframework.beans.factory.config.BeanPostProcessor` , `org.springframework.context.ApplicationContext` por ejemplo) no se ejecutarÃĄn. En cuanto a la inyecciÃģn de dependencias en particular, Quarkus utiliza un mecanismo de inyecciÃģn de dependencias (denominado ArC) basado en la especificaciÃģn link:https://jakarta.ee/specifications/cdi/4.1/jakarta-cdi-spec-4.1.html[Jakarta Contexts and Dependency Injection 4.1] . Si desea obtener mÃĄs informaciÃģn al respecto, le recomendamos que lea la xref:cdi.adoc[introducciÃģn de Quarkus a CDI] y la xref:cdi-reference.adoc#arc-configuration-reference[guÃ­a de referencia CDI] Las diversas caracterÃ­sticas de prueba de Spring Boot no son compatibles con Quarkus. Para realizar pruebas, por favor, consulte la xref:getting-started-testing.adoc[guÃ­a de pruebas] de Quarkus."

